1 0 0 1 54 744 Tm (C++ Upstox Delivery Trading Bot) Tj
/F1 10 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 723 Tm (Version 1.0 | Prepared on 30 June 2026) Tj
1 0 0 1 54 709 Tm (This document is a planning and software architecture artifact. It is not financial advice) Tj
1 0 0 1 54 695 Tm (and does not guarantee trading profits. Live trading must be enabled only after dry-run) Tj
1 0 0 1 54 681 Tm (validation, broker compliance checks, and user approval.) Tj
/F2 15 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 667 Tm (1. Introduction) Tj
/F2 12 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 648 Tm (1.1 Purpose) Tj
/F1 10 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 632 Tm (This Software Requirements Specification defines the functional, non-functional,) Tj
1 0 0 1 54 618 Tm (architectural, safety, and compliance requirements for a C++ automated delivery trading bot) Tj
1 0 0 1 54 604 Tm (using the latest Upstox APIs. The system will read company instrument keys from a CSV file,) Tj
1 0 0 1 54 590 Tm (analyze market data using configurable strategies, and automate delivery buy and sell orders) Tj
1 0 0 1 54 576 Tm (after risk validation.) Tj
1 0 0 1 54 562 Tm (The first implementation shall prioritize dry-run behavior, auditability, safety gates,) Tj
1 0 0 1 54 548 Tm (modular strategy design, and correctness before enabling live order placement.) Tj
/F2 12 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 534 Tm (1.2 Intended Users) Tj
/F1 10 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 518 Tm (- Individual trader or developer operating the bot from an approved Upstox API) Tj
1 0 0 1 54 504 Tm (  environment.) Tj
1 0 0 1 54 490 Tm (- Software developer extending strategy modules in C++.) Tj
1 0 0 1 54 476 Tm (- System operator reviewing logs, dry-run decisions, and order audit records.) Tj
/F2 12 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 462 Tm (1.3 Scope) Tj
/F1 10 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 446 Tm (The system is limited to Indian equity delivery trading through Upstox. It will not support) Tj
1 0 0 1 54 432 Tm (intraday, margin trading, futures and options, commodities, mutual funds, high-frequency) Tj
1 0 0 1 54 418 Tm (trading, or multi-broker routing in version 1.) Tj
/F2 12 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 404 Tm (1.4 Definitions) Tj
/F2 9 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 388 Tm (Term: Meaning) Tj
/F1 9 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 375 Tm (Delivery: Equity order intended to settle into holdings. Upstox product code D.) Tj
1 0 0 1 54 362 Tm (Instrument Key: Canonical Upstox identifier such as NSE_EQ|INE002A01018.) Tj
1 0 0 1 54 349 Tm (LTP: Latest traded price.) Tj
1 0 0 1 54 336 Tm (OHLCV: Open, high, low, close, volume candle data.) Tj
1 0 0 1 54 323 Tm (Dry Run: Mode that executes all logic except live order placement.) Tj
1 0 0 1 54 310 Tm (Strategy: Module that evaluates market data and emits buy or sell signals.) Tj
/F2 15 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 297 Tm (2. Business Objectives) Tj
/F1 10 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 278 Tm (- Automate disciplined delivery buy and sell decisions based on defined strategies.) Tj
1 0 0 1 54 264 Tm (- Avoid missed profit exits by prioritizing sell orders when target or risk exits trigger.) Tj
1 0 0 1 54 250 Tm (- Make strategy development modular so RSI divergence, trendlines, breakouts, and future) Tj
1 0 0 1 54 236 Tm (  methods can be added cleanly.) Tj
1 0 0 1 54 222 Tm (- Protect capital through strict risk checks, dry-run defaults, and complete audit logs.) Tj
ET
endstream
